182     /**
183      * Creates a new ServerPlayer.
184      *
185      * @param game The <code>Game</code> this object belongs to.
186      * @param admin Whether the player is the game administrator or not.
187      * @param nation The nation of the <code>Player</code>.
188      * @param socket The socket to the player's client.
189      * @param connection The <code>Connection</code> for the socket.
190      */
191     public ServerPlayer(Game game, boolean admin, Nation nation,
192                         Socket socket, Connection connection) {
193         super(game);
194
195         if (nation == null) throw new IllegalArgumentException("Null nation");
196         final Specification spec = getSpecification();
197
198         this.name = nation.getRulerName();
199         this.admin = admin;
200         this.nationId = nation.getId();
201         this.immigration = 0;
202         if (nation.isUnknownEnemy()) { // virtual "enemy privateer" player
203             this.nationType = null;
204             this.playerType = PlayerType.COLONIAL;
205             this.europe = null;
206             this.monarch = null;
207             this.gold = 0;
208             this.setAI(true);
209         } else if (nation.getType() != null) {
210             this.nationType = nation.getType();
211             try {
212                 addFeatures(nationType);
213             } catch (Throwable error) {
214                 error.printStackTrace();
215             }
216             if (nationType.isEuropean()) {
217                 /*
218                  * Setting the amount of gold to
219                  * "getGameOptions().getInteger(GameOptions.STARTING_MONEY)"
220                  *
221                  * just before starting the game. See
222                  * "net.sf.freecol.server.control.PreGameController".
223                  */
224                 this.playerType = (nationType.isREF()) ? PlayerType.ROYAL
225                     : PlayerType.COLONIAL;
226                 this.europe = new ServerEurope(game, this);
227                 initializeHighSeas();
228                 if (this.playerType == PlayerType.COLONIAL) {
229                     this.monarch = new Monarch(game, this);
230                     // In BR#2615 misiulo reports that Col1 players start
231                     // with 2 crosses.  This is surprising, but you could
232                     // argue that some level of religious unrest might
233                     // contribute to the fact there is an expedition to
234                     // the new world underway.
235                     this.immigration = spec.getInteger(GameOptions.PLAYER_IMMIGRATION_BONUS);
236                 }
237                 this.gold = 0;
238             } else { // indians
239                 this.playerType = PlayerType.NATIVE;
240                 this.gold = Player.GOLD_NOT_ACCOUNTED;
241             }
242         } else {
243             throw new IllegalArgumentException("Bogus nation: " + nation);
244         }
245         this.market = new Market(getGame(), this);
246         this.liberty = 0;
247         this.currentFather = null;
248
249         this.socket = socket;
250         this.setConnection(connection);
251     }

313     /**
314      * Send a message to the player, and return the resulting message.

316      * @param game The <code>Game</code> to build the return message in.

319      */

322     }
323     
324     /**
325      * Send an element to this player.
326      * Do not use (sole use in send() above). This will go away.
327      *
328      * @param request An <code>Element</code> containing the update.
329      */
330     private void askElement(Element request) {
331         if (!isConnected()) return;
332
333         while (request != null) {
334             Element reply;
335             try {
336                 reply = this.connection.ask(request);
337                 if (reply == null) break;
338             } catch (IOException e) {
339                 logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Could not send \""
340                     + request.getTagName() + "\"-message.", e);
341                 break;
342             }
343
344             try {
345                 request = this.connection.handle(reply);
346             } catch (FreeColException fce) {
347                 logger.log(Level.WARNING, "Exception processing reply \""
348                     + reply.getTagName() + "\"-message.", fce);
349                 break;
350             }
351         }
352     }

355      * Convenience function to create a client error message, log it,
356      * and wrap it into a change set.

361     public ChangeSet clientError(String message) {

370     }

407     /**
408      * Performs initial randomizations for this player.
409      *
410      * @param random A pseudo-random number source.
411      */
412     public void randomizeGame(Random random) {
413         if (!isEuropean() || isREF() || isUnknownEnemy()) return;
414         final Specification spec = getGame().getSpecification();
415
416         // Set initial immigration target
417         int i0 = spec.getInteger(GameOptions.INITIAL_IMMIGRATION);
418         immigrationRequired = (int)applyModifiers((float)i0, null,
419             Modifier.RELIGIOUS_UNREST_BONUS);
420
421         // Add initial gold
422         modifyGold(spec.getInteger(GameOptions.STARTING_MONEY));
423
424         // Choose starting immigrants
425         ((ServerEurope)getEurope()).initializeMigration(random);
426
427         // Randomize the initial market prices
428         Market market = getMarket();
429         StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
430         boolean changed = false;
431         for (GoodsType type : spec.getGoodsTypeList()) {
432             String prefix = "model.option."
433                 + type.getSuffix("model.goods.");
434             // these options are not available for all goods types
435             if (spec.hasOption(prefix + ".minimumPrice")
436                 && spec.hasOption(prefix + ".maximumPrice")) {
437                 int min = spec.getInteger(prefix + ".minimumPrice");
438                 int max = spec.getInteger(prefix + ".maximumPrice");
439                 if (max < min) { // User error
440                     int bad = min;
441                     min = max;
442                     max = bad;
443                 } else if (max == min) continue;
444                 int add = randomInt(null, null, random, max - min);
445                 if (add > 0) {
446                     market.setInitialPrice(type, min + add);
447                     market.update(type);
448                     market.flushPriceChange(type);
449                     sb.append(", ").append(type.getId())
450                         .append(" -> ").append(min + add);
451                     changed = true;
452                 }
453             }
454         }
455         if (changed) {
456             logger.finest("randomizeGame(" + getId() + ") initial prices: "
457                 + sb.toString().substring(2));
458         }
459     }

461     /**
462      * Checks if this player has died.
463      *
464      * @return Negative if the player is dead, zero if they are ok,
465      *      positive non-zero if the server should auto-recruit
466      *      colonist units to keep this player alive.
467      */
468     public int checkForDeath() {
469         if (isUnknownEnemy()) return IS_ALIVE;
470         final Specification spec = getGame().getSpecification();
471         /*
472          * Die if: (isNative && (no colonies or units))
473          *      || ((rebel or independent) && !(has coastal colony))
474          *      || (isREF && !(rebel nation left) && (all units in Europe))
475          *      || ((no units in New World)
476          *         && ((year > 1600) || (cannot get a unit from Europe)))
477          */
478         switch (getPlayerType()) {
479         case NATIVE: // All natives units are viable
480             return (getUnits().isEmpty()) ? IS_DEAD : IS_ALIVE;
481
482         case COLONIAL: // Handle the hard case below
483             break;
484
485         case REBEL: case INDEPENDENT:
486             // Post-declaration European player needs a coastal colony
487             // and can not hope for resupply from Europe.
488             return (getNumberOfPorts() > 0) ? IS_ALIVE : IS_DEAD;
489
490         case ROYAL:
491             return (getRebels().isEmpty()) ? IS_DEAD : IS_ALIVE;
492
493         case UNDEAD:
494             return (getUnits().isEmpty()) ? IS_DEAD : IS_ALIVE;
495
496         default:
497             throw new IllegalStateException("Bogus player type");
498         }
499
500         // Quick check for a colony.  Do not log, this is the common case.
501         if (!getColonies().isEmpty()) return IS_ALIVE;
502
503         // Do not kill the observing player during a debug run.
504         if (!isAI() && FreeColDebugger.getDebugRunTurns() >= 0) return IS_ALIVE;
505
506         // Do not kill the unknown enemy!
507         if (isUnknownEnemy()) return IS_ALIVE;
508
509         // Traverse player units, look for valid carriers, colonists,
510         // carriers with units, carriers with goods.
511         boolean hasCarrier = false, hasColonist = false, hasEmbarked = false,
512             hasGoods = false;
513         for (Unit unit : getUnits()) {
514             if (unit.isCarrier()) {
515                 if (unit.hasGoodsCargo()) hasGoods = true;
516                 hasCarrier = true;
517                 continue;
518             }
519
520             // Must be able to found new colony or capture units
521             if (!unit.isColonist() && !unit.isOffensiveUnit()) continue;
522             hasColonist = true;
523
524             // Verify if unit is in new world, or on a carrier in new world
525             Unit carrier;
526             if ((carrier = unit.getCarrier()) != null) {
527                 if (carrier.hasTile()) {
528                     logger.info(getName() + " alive, unit " + unit.getId()
529                         + " (embarked) on map.");
530                     return IS_ALIVE;
531                 }
532                 hasEmbarked = true;
533             }
534             if (unit.hasTile() && !unit.isInMission()) {
535                 logger.info(getName() + " alive, unit " + unit.getId()
536                     + " on map.");
537                 return IS_ALIVE;
538             }
539         }
540         // The player does not have any valid units or settlements on the map.
541
542         int mandatory = spec.getInteger(GameOptions.MANDATORY_COLONY_YEAR);
543         if (getGame().getTurn().getYear() >= mandatory) {
544             // After the season cutover year there must be a presence
545             // in the New World.
546             logger.info(getName() + " dead, no presence >= " + mandatory);
547             return IS_DEAD;
548         }
549
550         // No problems, unit available on carrier but off map, or goods
551         // available to be sold.
552         if (hasEmbarked) {
553             logger.info(getName() + " alive, has embarked unit.");
554             return IS_ALIVE;
555         } else if (hasGoods) {
556             logger.info(getName() + " alive, has cargo.");
557             return IS_ALIVE;
558         }
559
560         // It is necessary to still have a carrier.
561         final Europe europe = getEurope();
562         int goldNeeded = 0;
563         if (!hasCarrier) {
564             int price = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
565             if (europe != null) {
566                 for (UnitType type
567                          : spec.getUnitTypesWithAbility(Ability.NAVAL_UNIT)) {
568                     int p = europe.getUnitPrice(type);
569                     if (p != UNDEFINED && p < price) price = p;
570                 }
571             }
572             if (price == Integer.MAX_VALUE || !checkGold(price)) {
573                 logger.info(getName() + " dead, can not buy carrier.");
574                 return IS_DEAD;
575             }
576             goldNeeded += price;
577         }
578
579         // A colonist is required.
580         if (hasColonist) {
581             logger.info(getName() + " alive, has waiting colonist.");
582             return IS_ALIVE;
583         } else if (europe == null) {
584             logger.info(getName() + " dead, can not recruit.");
585             return IS_DEAD;
586         }
587         UnitType unitType = null;
588         int price = europe.getRecruitPrice();
589         for (UnitType type : spec.getUnitTypesWithAbility(Ability.FOUND_COLONY)) {
590             int p = europe.getUnitPrice(type);
591             if (p != UNDEFINED && p < price) price = p;
592         }
593         goldNeeded += price;
594         if (checkGold(goldNeeded)) {
595             logger.info(getName() + " alive, can buy colonist.");
596             return IS_ALIVE;
597         }
598
599         // Col1 auto-recruits a unit in Europe if you run out before
600         // the cutover year.
601         logger.info(getName() + " survives by autorecruit.");
602         return AUTORECRUIT;
603     }
604
605     /**
606      * Check if a REF player has been defeated and should surrender.
607      *
608      * @return True if this REF player has been defeated.
609      */
610     public boolean checkForREFDefeat() {
611         if (!isREF()) {
612             throw new IllegalStateException("Checking for REF player defeat when player not REF.");
613         }
614
615         // No one to fight?  Either the rebels are dead, or the REF
616         // was already defeated and the rebels are independent.
617         // Either way, it does not need to surrender.
618         if (getRebels().isEmpty()) return false;
619
620         // Not defeated if there are settlements.
621         if (hasSettlements()) return false;
622
623         // Not defeated if there is a non-zero navy and enough land units.
624         final int landREFUnitsRequired = 7; // FIXME: magic number
625         final CombatModel cm = getGame().getCombatModel();
626         boolean naval = false;
627         int land = 0;
628         int power = 0;
629         for (Unit u : getUnits()) {
630             if (u.isNaval()) naval = true; else {
631                 if (u.hasAbility(Ability.REF_UNIT)) {
632                     land++;
633                     power += cm.getOffencePower(u, null);
634                 }
635             }
636         }
637         if (naval && land >= landREFUnitsRequired) return false;
638
639         // Still not defeated as long as military strength is greater
640         // than the rebels.
641         Stream<Unit> us = getRebels().stream()
642             .flatMap(rebel -> rebel.getUnits().stream());
643         int rebelPower = (int)sumDouble(us, u -> !u.isNaval(),
644                                         u -> cm.getOffencePower(u, null));
645         if (power > rebelPower) return false;
646
647         // REF is defeated
648         return true;
649     }

651     /**
652      * Kill off a player and clear out its remains.
653      *
654      * +vis: Albeit killing the player makes visibility changes moot.
655      * +til: Fixes the appearance changes too.
656      *
657      * @param cs A <code>ChangeSet</code> to update.
658      */
659     public void csKill(ChangeSet cs) {
660         setDead(true);
661         cs.addPartial(See.all(), this, "dead");
662         cs.addDead(this);
663
664         // Clean up missions and remove tension/alarm/stance.
665         for (Player other : getGame().getLivePlayers(this)) {
666             if (isEuropean() && other.isIndian()) {
667                 for (IndianSettlement s : other.getIndianSettlements()) {
668                     if (s.hasMissionary(this)) {
669                         ((ServerIndianSettlement)s).csKillMissionary(null, cs);
670                     }
671                     s.getTile().cacheUnseen();//+til
672                     ((ServerIndianSettlement)s).removeAlarm(this);//-til
673                 }
674                 other.removeTension(this);
675             }
676             other.setStance(this, null);
677         }
678
679         // Remove settlements.  Update formerly owned tiles.
680         List<Settlement> settlements = getSettlements();
681         while (!settlements.isEmpty()) {
682             csDisposeSettlement(settlements.remove(0), cs);
683         }
684
685         // Clean up remaining tile ownerships
686         for (Tile tile : getGame().getMap().getAllTiles()) {
687             if (tile.getOwner() == this) {
688                 tile.cacheUnseen();//+til
689                 tile.changeOwnership(null, null);//-til
690                 cs.add(See.perhaps().always(this), tile);
691             }
692         }
693
694         // Remove units
695         List<Unit> units = getUnits();
696         while (!units.isEmpty()) {
697             Unit u = units.remove(0);
698             if (u.hasTile()) cs.add(See.perhaps(), u.getTile());
699             cs.addRemove(See.perhaps().always(this),
700                          u.getLocation(), u);//-vis(this)
701             u.dispose();
702         }
703
704         // Remove European stuff
705         if (market != null) {
706             market.dispose();
707             market = null;
708         }
709         if (monarch != null) {
710             monarch.dispose();
711             monarch = null;
712         }
713         if (europe != null) {
714             europe.dispose();
715             europe = null;
716         }
717         currentFather = null;
718         if (foundingFathers != null) foundingFathers.clear();
719         if (offeredFathers != null) offeredFathers.clear();
720         // FIXME: stance and tension?
721         if (tradeRoutes != null) tradeRoutes.clear();
722         // Retaining model messages for now
723         // Retaining history for now
724         if (lastSales != null) lastSales = null;
725         featureContainer.clear();
726
727         invalidateCanSeeTiles();//+vis(this)
728     }

730     /**
731      * Withdraw a player from the new world.
732      *
733      * @param cs A <code>ChangeSet</code> to update.
734      */
735     public void csWithdraw(ChangeSet cs) {
736         String key = (isEuropean() && getPlayerType() == PlayerType.COLONIAL)
737             ? "model.player.dead.european"
738             : "model.player.dead.native";
739         cs.addMessage(See.all(),
740             new ModelMessage(MessageType.FOREIGN_DIPLOMACY, key, this)
741                 .addStringTemplate("%nation%", getNationLabel()));
742         Game game = getGame();
743         cs.addGlobalHistory(game,
744             new HistoryEvent(game.getTurn(),
745                              HistoryEvent.HistoryEventType.NATION_DESTROYED, null)
746                 .addStringTemplate("%nation%", getNationLabel()));
747         csKill(cs);
748     }

759     /**
760      * Checks whether the current founding father has been recruited.
761      *
762      * @return The new founding father, or null if none available or ready.
763      */
764     public FoundingFather checkFoundingFather() {
765         FoundingFather father = null;
766         if (currentFather != null) {
767             int extraLiberty = getRemainingFoundingFatherCost();
768             if (extraLiberty <= 0) {
769                 boolean overflow = getSpecification()
770                     .getBoolean(GameOptions.SAVE_PRODUCTION_OVERFLOW);
771                 setLiberty((overflow) ? -extraLiberty : 0);
772                 father = currentFather;
773                 currentFather = null;
774             }
775         }
776         return father;
777     }

779     /**
780      * Checks whether to start recruiting a founding father.
781      *
782      * @return True if a new father should be chosen.
783      */
784     public boolean canRecruitFoundingFather() {
785         Specification spec = getGame().getSpecification();
786         switch (getPlayerType()) {
787         case COLONIAL:
788             break;
789         case REBEL: case INDEPENDENT:
790             if (!spec.getBoolean(GameOptions.CONTINUE_FOUNDING_FATHER_RECRUITMENT)) return false;
791             break;
792         default:
793             return false;
794         }
795         return canHaveFoundingFathers() && currentFather == null
796             && hasSettlements()
797             && getFatherCount() < spec.getFoundingFathers().size();
798     }

800     /**
801      * Build a list of random FoundingFathers, one per type.
802      * Do not include any the player has or are not available.
803      *
804      * @param random A pseudo-random number source.
805      * @return A list of FoundingFathers.
806      */
807     public List<FoundingFather> getRandomFoundingFathers(Random random) {
808         // Build weighted random choice for each father type
809         final Game game = getGame();
810         final Specification spec = game.getSpecification();
811         final int age = game.getAge();
812         EnumMap<FoundingFatherType, List<RandomChoice<FoundingFather>>> choices
813             = new EnumMap<>(FoundingFatherType.class);
814         for (FoundingFather father : spec.getFoundingFathers()) {
815             if (!hasFather(father) && father.isAvailableTo(this)) {
816                 FoundingFatherType type = father.getType();
817                 List<RandomChoice<FoundingFather>> rc = choices.get(type);
818                 if (rc == null) rc = new ArrayList<>();
819                 int weight = father.getWeight(age);
820                 rc.add(new RandomChoice<>(father, weight));
821                 choices.put(father.getType(), rc);
822             }
823         }
824
825         // Select one from each father type
826         List<FoundingFather> randomFathers = new ArrayList<>();
827         LogBuilder lb = new LogBuilder(64);
828         lb.add("Random fathers for ", getDebugName());
829         for (FoundingFatherType type : FoundingFatherType.values()) {
830             List<RandomChoice<FoundingFather>> rc = choices.get(type);
831             if (rc != null) {
832                 FoundingFather f = RandomChoice.getWeightedRandom(logger,
833                     "Choose founding father", rc, random);
834                 if (f != null) {
835                     randomFathers.add(f);
836                     lb.add(":", f.getSuffix());
837                 }
838             }
839         }
840         lb.log(logger, Level.INFO);
841         return randomFathers;
842     }

854     /**
855      * Update the current score for this player.
856      *
857      * Known incompatibility with the Col1 manual:
858      * ``In addition, you get one point per liberty bell produced
859      *   after foreign intervention''
860      * However you are already getting a point per liberty bell
861      * produced, so this implies you get no further liberty after
862      * declaring independence!?, but it can then start again if the
863      * foreign intervention happens (penalizing players who quickly
864      * thrash the REF:-S).  Whatever this really means, it is
865      * incompatible with our extensions to allow playing on (and
866      * defeating other Europeans), so for now at least just leave the
867      * simple liberty==score rule in place.
868      *
869      * @return True if the player score changed.
870      */
871     public boolean updateScore() {
872         int oldScore = this.score;
873         this.score = sum(getUnits(), u -> u.getType().getScoreValue())
874             + sum(getColonies(), Colony::getLiberty)
875             + SCORE_FOUNDING_FATHER * getFathers().size();
876         int gold = getGold();
877         if (gold != GOLD_NOT_ACCOUNTED) {
878             this.score += (int)Math.floor(SCORE_GOLD * gold);
879         }
880         
881         int bonus = 0;
882         for (HistoryEvent h : getHistory()) {
883             if (getId().equals(h.getPlayerId())) {
884                 switch (h.getEventType()) {
885                 case INDEPENDENCE:
886                     switch (h.getScore()) {
887                     case 0: bonus = SCORE_INDEPENDENCE_BONUS_FIRST; break;
888                     case 1: bonus = SCORE_INDEPENDENCE_BONUS_SECOND; break;
889                     case 2: bonus = SCORE_INDEPENDENCE_BONUS_THIRD; break;
890                     default: bonus = 0; break;
891                     }
892                     break;
893                 default:
894                     this.score += h.getScore();
895                     break;
896                 }
897             }
898         }
899         this.score += (this.score * bonus) / 100;
900
901         return this.score != oldScore;
902     }

932     /**

1,002     /**
1,003      * Try to reassign the ownership of a collection of tiles.
1,004      *

1,006      * a large advantage.
1,007      *
1,008      * @param tiles The collection of <code>Tile</code>s to reassign.

1,011      *     when making claims.
1,012      */
1,013     private static void reassignTiles(Collection<Tile> tiles,
1,014                                       Player prefer,
1,015                                       Settlement avoid) {
1,016         HashMap<Settlement, Integer> votes = new HashMap<>();
1,017         HashMap<Tile, Settlement> claims = new HashMap<>();
1,018         Settlement claimant;
1,019         for (Tile tile : tiles) {
1,020             if (tile.isOccupied()) continue;
1,021             votes.clear();
1,022             for (Tile t : tile.getSurroundingTiles(1)) {
1,023                 claimant = t.getOwningSettlement();
1,024                 if (claimant != null
1,025                     // BR#3375773 found a case where tiles were
1,026                     // still owned by a settlement that had been
1,027                     // previously destroyed.  These should be gone, but...
1,028                     && !claimant.isDisposed()
1,029                     && claimant.getOwner() != null
1,030                     && claimant.getOwner().canOwnTile(tile)
1,031                     && (claimant.getOwner().isIndian()
1,032                         || claimant.getTile().getDistanceTo(tile)
1,033                         <= claimant.getRadius())) {
1,034                     // Weight claimant settlements:
1,035                     //   settlements owned by the same player
1,036                     //     > settlements owned by same type of player
1,037                     //     > other settlements
1,038                     int value = (prefer == null) ? 1
1,039                         : (claimant.getOwner() == prefer) ? 3
1,040                         : (claimant.getOwner().isEuropean()
1,041                             == prefer.isEuropean()) ? 2
1,042                         : 1;
1,043                     if (votes.get(claimant) != null) {
1,044                         value += votes.get(claimant);
1,045                     }
1,046                     votes.put(claimant, value);
1,047                 }
1,048             }
1,049             boolean lastResort = false;
1,050             int bestValue = 0;
1,051             claimant = null;
1,052             for (Entry<Settlement, Integer> entry : votes.entrySet()) {
1,053                 if (avoid == entry.getKey()) {
1,054                     lastResort = true;
1,055                     continue;
1,056                 }
1,057                 int value = entry.getValue();
1,058                 if (bestValue < value) {
1,059                     bestValue = value;
1,060                     claimant = entry.getKey();
1,061                 }
1,062             }
1,063             if (claimant == null && lastResort) claimant = avoid;
1,064             claims.put(tile, claimant);
1,065         }
1,066         for (Entry<Tile, Settlement> e : claims.entrySet()) {
1,067             Tile t = e.getKey();
1,068             if ((claimant = e.getValue()) == null) {
1,069                 t.changeOwnership(null, null);//-til
1,070             } else {
1,071                 ServerPlayer newOwner = (ServerPlayer)claimant.getOwner();
1,072                 t.changeOwnership(newOwner, claimant);//-til
1,073             }
1,074         }
1,075     }

3,530
3,531     /**
3,532      * Disposes of a settlement and reassign its tiles.
3,533      *
3,534      * +vis,til: Resolves the whole mess.
3,535      *
3,536      * @param settlement The <code>Settlement</code> under attack.
3,537      * @param cs A <code>ChangeSet</code> to update.
3,538      */
3,539     public void csDisposeSettlement(Settlement settlement, ChangeSet cs) {
3,540         logger.finest("Disposing of " + settlement.getName());
3,541         ServerPlayer owner = (ServerPlayer)settlement.getOwner();
3,542         Set<Tile> owned = settlement.getOwnedTiles();
3,543         for (Tile t : owned) t.cacheUnseen();//+til
3,544         Tile centerTile = settlement.getTile();
3,545         ServerPlayer missionaryOwner = null;
3,546         int radius = 0;
3,547
3,548         // Get rid of the any missionary first.
3,549         if (settlement instanceof ServerIndianSettlement) {
3,550             ServerIndianSettlement sis = (ServerIndianSettlement)settlement;
3,551             if (sis.hasMissionary()) {
3,552                 missionaryOwner = (ServerPlayer)sis.getMissionary().getOwner();
3,553                 radius = sis.getMissionaryLineOfSight();
3,554                 sis.csKillMissionary(true, cs);
3,555             }
3,556         }
3,557             
3,558         // Get it off the map and off the owners list.
3,559         settlement.exciseSettlement();//-vis(owner),-til
3,560         owner.removeSettlement(settlement);
3,561         if (owner.hasSettlement(settlement)) {
3,562             throw new IllegalStateException("Still has settlement: "
3,563                 + settlement);
3,564         }
3,565
3,566         // Reassign the tiles owned by the settlement, if possible
3,567         reassignTiles(owned, owner, null);
3,568
3,569         See vis = See.perhaps().always(owner);
3,570         if (missionaryOwner != null) vis.except(missionaryOwner);
3,571         cs.add(vis, owned);
3,572         cs.addRemove(vis, centerTile, settlement);//-vis(owner)
3,573         settlement.dispose();
3,574         owner.invalidateCanSeeTiles();//+vis(owner)
3,575
3,576         // Former missionary owner knows that the settlement fell.
3,577         if (missionaryOwner != null) {
3,578             List<Tile> surrounding = transform(centerTile.getSurroundingTiles(1, radius),
3,579                 t -> !owned.contains(t), Collectors.toList());
3,580             cs.add(See.only(missionaryOwner), owned);
3,581             cs.add(See.only(missionaryOwner), surrounding);
3,582             cs.addRemove(See.only(missionaryOwner), centerTile, settlement);
3,583             missionaryOwner.invalidateCanSeeTiles();//+vis(missionaryOwner)
3,584             for (Tile t : surrounding) t.cacheUnseen(missionaryOwner);
3,585         }
3,586
3,587         // Recache, should only show now cleared tiles to former owner.
3,588         for (Tile t : owned) t.cacheUnseen();
3,589         // Center tile is special for native settlements.  Because
3,590         // native settlement tiles are *always* cached, the cache
3,591         // needs to be completely cleared for players that can see the
3,592         // settlement is gone.
3,593         if (settlement instanceof IndianSettlement) centerTile.seeTile();
3,594         if (missionaryOwner != null) centerTile.seeTile(missionaryOwner);
3,595     }

4,474     /**
4,475      * Change the owner of a unit or dispose of it if the change is
4,476      * impossible.  Move the unit to a new location if necessary.
4,477      * Also handle disappearance of any carried units that will now be
4,478      * invisible to the new owner.
4,479      *
4,480      * -vis(owner,newOwner)
4,481      *
4,482      * @param unit The <code>Unit</code> to change ownership of.
4,483      * @param newOwner The new owning <code>ServerPlayer</code>.
4,484      * @param change An optional accompanying <code>ChangeType</code>.
4,485      * @param loc A optional new <code>Location</code> for the unit.
4,486      * @param cs A <code>ChangeSet</code> to update.
4,487      * @return True if the new owner can have this unit.
4,488      */
4,489     public boolean csChangeOwner(Unit unit, ServerPlayer newOwner,
4,490                                  ChangeType change, Location loc,
4,491                                  ChangeSet cs) {
4,492         if (newOwner == this) return true; // No transfer needed
4,493
4,494         final Tile oldTile = unit.getTile();
4,495         UnitType mainType = unit.getTypeChange(change, newOwner);
4,496         if (mainType == null) mainType = unit.getType(); // No change needed.
4,497         if (!mainType.isAvailableTo(newOwner)) { // Can not have this unit.
4,498             cs.addRemove(See.perhaps().always(this), oldTile, unit);
4,499             unit.dispose();
4,500             return false;
4,501         }
4,502
4,503         for (Unit u : unit.getUnitList()) {
4,504             UnitType type = u.getTypeChange(change, newOwner);
4,505             if (type == null) type = u.getType();
4,506             if (!type.isAvailableTo(newOwner)) {
4,507                 cs.addRemove(See.only(this), unit, u);
4,508                 u.dispose();
4,509             } else {
4,510                 if (!u.changeType(type)) {
4,511                     throw new IllegalStateException("Type change failure: "
4,512                         + u + " -> " + type);
4,513                 }
4,514             }
4,515         }
4,516         if (mainType != unit.getType() && !unit.changeType(mainType)) {
4,517             throw new IllegalStateException("Type change failure: " + unit
4,518                 + " -> " + mainType);
4,519         }
4,520         unit.changeOwner(newOwner);
4,521         if (loc != null) unit.setLocation(loc);
4,522         if (unit.isCarrier()) {
4,523             cs.addRemoves(See.only(this), unit, unit.getUnitList());
4,524         }
4,525         cs.add(See.only(newOwner), newOwner.exploreForUnit(unit));
4,526         return true;
4,527     }
